---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Trust - AnswerLayer"
  description="How AnswerLayer keeps your data secure with VPC deployment, guardrails, and compliance-ready infrastructure."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h1 class="mb-lg">Trust</h1>
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width: 600px;">
        Security isn't an add-on. AnswerLayer is built for organizations that can't
        compromise on data protection.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Data Stays in Your Cloud -->
  <section class="section-sm" >
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="trust-section">
        <h2>Data Stays in Your Cloud</h2>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>VPC deployment is standard</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Not a premium feature, not an afterthought. AnswerLayer is designed to run
              in your infrastructure from day one.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Query execution in your environment</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              SQL runs against your database, in your cloud. Results never traverse
              external networks.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Only metadata for generation</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Schema structure and data samples power the semantic layer generation.
              Your actual data rows stay where they are.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Static outbound IP</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Whitelist a single IP address in your firewall. No dynamic ranges,
              no guesswork.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Guardrails at Every Level -->
  <section class="section-sm" >
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="trust-section">
        <h2>Guardrails at Every Level</h2>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>PII detection with confidence scoring</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              AI-powered detection scans columns for emails, phone numbers, SSNs, and other
              sensitive data. Each detection comes with a confidence score, and you can
              override any decision.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Query validation blocks dangerous operations</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              DROP, DELETE, TRUNCATE, ALTER are blocked by default. Generated SQL is validated
              against your schema before execution.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Row limits prevent runaway queries</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Configurable caps on result set size. Default is 10,000 rows—enough for
              analysis, not enough for exfiltration.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Timeout protection</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Queries time out after 2 minutes by default. Long-running operations
              are stopped before they impact your database.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Credential Security -->
  <section class="section-sm" >
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="trust-section">
        <h2>Credential Security</h2>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>PBKDF2 + Fernet encryption</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Database credentials are encrypted at rest using industry-standard
              algorithms. Not stored in plaintext, ever.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Cloud KMS key management</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Encryption keys are managed through your cloud provider's KMS—GCP,
              AWS, or Azure. You control access.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Decrypted only at connection time</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Credentials are decrypted when connecting to your database and immediately
              discarded after. No credential caching.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Access Controls -->
  <section class="section-sm" >
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="trust-section">
        <h2>Access Controls</h2>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Organization-level isolation</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Each organization's data is completely isolated. No cross-tenant access,
              no shared resources.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Role-based access from your identity provider</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Sync roles from Okta, Azure AD, or your existing identity provider.
              SSO via SAML 2.0 and OpenID Connect.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Full audit logging</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Every query, every API call, every configuration change is logged.
              Export to your SIEM for compliance reporting.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Compliance -->
  <section class="section-sm" >
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="trust-section">
        <h2>Compliance</h2>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>SOC 2 Type II</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              In progress. Built on SOC 2-compliant infrastructure from day one.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>GDPR ready</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              Data processing agreements available. EU data residency options
              for VPC deployments.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-item">
          <span class="trust-icon">✓</span>
          <div>
            <strong>HIPAA considerations</strong>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm mt-xs">
              VPC deployments can be configured for HIPAA compliance.
              BAA available for enterprise customers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <section class="section text-center" >
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2 class="mb-md">Security Questions?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-lg">
        Contact our security team for detailed documentation, penetration test reports,
        or to schedule a security review.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:security@getanswerlayer.com" class="btn btn-link">security@getanswerlayer.com</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
